<html>
<head>
<title>
 California's County and City Hispanic Census Analysis
</title>
</head>
<body>
<center><big>
California's County and City Hispanic Census Analysis
</big></center><p>
<ol>
<li>Download the Excel 5.0 files.
	<ul>
	<li><a href=raw_data.xls> raw_data.xls</a> Master census raw data in Excel format.
 </ul>
<ul>
	<li><a href=cntydata.xls> cntydata.xls</a> Analyzed county data in Excel format.
	<li><a href=citydata.xls> citydata.xls</a> Analyzed city data in Excel format.
	</ul>
<li><a href=summary.htm>Summary</a>
<li>View the County Data; this is a look at the <i>cntydata.xls</i> file.
	<ul>
	<li> County data sorted by <a href=cntyhspn.htm>percent Hispanic.</a>
	<li> County data sorted by <a href=cntychng.htm>percent change from 1980 to 1990.</a>
	</ul>
<li>View the City Data; this is a look at the <i>citydata.xls</i> file.
	<ul>
	<li>City data sorted by <a href=cityhspn.htm> percent Hispanic.</a>
	<li>City data sorted by <a href=citychng.htm> percent change from 1980 to 1990.</a>
	<li>
	<ul>
	<li>Cities greater than <a href=city100+.htm>100,000 </a>in population.
	<li>Cities between <a href=city100.htm>50,000 to 100,000</a> in population.
	<li>Cities between <a href=city50.htm>25,000 to 50,000</a> in population.
	<li>Cities less than <a href=city25-1.htm>25,000</a> in population.
	</ul>
	</ul>
</ol>	
<p>
<hr>
<a href=http://www.dof.ca.gov/>Source: California Dept. of Finance, State Census Data Center</a><br>
